http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/CBI-inquiry-against-two-serving-Major-generals-for-disproportionate-assets/article14024713.ece

The Defence Ministry has ordered an inquiry by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) against two serving Major Generals in the Army to probe disproportionate assets.The officers in question are Maj. Gen. Ashok Kumar from the Army Service Corps (ASC) and Maj. Gen. S.S. Lamba from the Army Ordinance Corps (AOC).Defence Ministry sources on Thursday confirmed the development and said the inquiry was ordered by Defence Minister Manohar Parrikar.CBI sources said that they have just received the communication but are yet to go through the files.Allegations of bribe had surfaced in promotions to the rank of Lieutenant General after the Army Promotion Board submitted its recommendations to the ministry.Incidentally both the officers were awarded Ati Vishisht Seva Medal (AVSM) in 2015 by the President of India for distinguished service.